Who loves ya baby :)<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#F5F5DC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utroydaedagor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Troy Daedagor</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>82</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>5/10/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>11:30:18 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re:  Ragefire spawns:  reservation/rotation list</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Fay is doing a great job. I would hate to think what position we would be in if she did not run this list. Even if Verant did allow GM's to run it I hardly see how they could do any better.<br>
<br>
That being said is there any validity in saying that those without a pearl make the list seem suspect? I think there is to a small extent. I also understand how it happened and would hate to see anyone punished for a rule change. So maybe some discussion to see if we as clerics think it should be altered at all would be good. I am not advocating any of these but merely posting ideas that may allow this list to continue to be a success.<br>
<br>
The main injustice with the list would seem to be that those with pearls are so far behind those without them. How would you feel in their place? Yes they have plenty of time to finish before their turns come up but still I think you can see what I am talking about. So what should/could be done to remedy this?<br>
<br>
One suggestion would be to move all with pearls up in line while keeping those on the list without the pearl. Then set a deadline for the pearless to get the pearl. You could do it one of two ways.<br>
 a) As they get the pearl they are moved up on this list. This would place alot of initiative on getting it done because it would allow some of those with no pearl to pass up some of the others with no pearl.<br>
 b) Or they keep their positions but the ones that do not get the pearls are removed at the deadline. With this option NO ONE would fall very many places unless they just did not get the pearl at all.<br>
<br>
Does that make sense? It would place initiative on getting the Pearl and make the list look better in the process. <br>
<br>
Another option would be just to place a deadline for those on the list to get their pearl or be removed. Say one month or something. Again this would create initiative to get the pearl. After one month all those left on the list would have a P after their name.<br>
<br>
Last option. Leave it how it is, shut up, and dont worry about it.<br>
<br>
The ONLY reason I bring this up is because it has to hurt those that are finished with pearl in hand to see so many infront of them that concievably may have not even started the quest. If we start getting a bunch of disgruntled clerics then the list has a higher probability of failing and that is the last thing I would ever want to see.<br>
<br>
I also think that swapping places should only be done between the cleric up and the cleric behind them. I can really see no good reason for people to be able to move around in the list if everyone has there pearl unless they cannot do Rage when there time comes up. For instance if someone will be out of town when their turn at Rage is up then they could post to skip them until they return. Also with no swapping if someone leaves the game it will just be a bonus that everyone gets to move up a slot.<br>
<br>
I hope no one takes this the wrong way. The last thing I would want to see is cleric removed from the list, well almost the last thing. The last thing I want to see is the list ever fail.<br>
<br>
I apologize if this was in poor taste for me to bring up when the list is going so well, I just want to head off trouble before it starts if at all possible.<br>
