The Limpstick Resser<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CCCCCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueayenaf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eayenaf</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>2</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>5/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>6:52:06 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re:  Ragefire spawns:  reservation/rotation list</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Thank you all for your timely replies and especially for Fayenae's honesty and integrity.  As I said in my earlier post, in no way was I questioning Fayenae's ability or integrity.  I know that no GM would ever give us real customer support; my previous comments were more rhetoric than anything.  However, I would like it if they did.<br>
<br>
I do have a few more comments that I would like to add to the fray of discussion.<br>
<br>
First, the lack of communication to clerics beginning the quest.  How are they supposed to know about the list?  How are they supposed to know that they are supposed to get on this list before they start camping Ragefire?  Is there a way to communicate the need to be on the list other than putting up with the dunder heads at the spawn that won't show any consideration for lack of knowledge on this spawn's protocol?<br>
<br>
Second, I agree with Troy that the clerics on the list without pearls should be given a time frame to work within.  One month should be a sufficient amount of time for those on the list without pearls to get them (the fact that I go that far even surprises me), however, there are some that do not have that long because they should get to the top of the list before then, Bijinko being the first of that category.  For those that reach the top without a pearl, I suggest removing them until they do get their pearl.  When they do, they should be put at the back of the list.  Some of you may wonder why I seem to be so harsh.  I would compare having the pearl to going to the store to buy something.  Imagine, you get in line to buy your items only to discover that you don't have any money on you.  What are your options?  1) Get out of line, go home, get your money, then get at the back of the line or 2) borrow the necessary materials from someone else so that you don't have to resort to option number one.  Unfortunately in our case, the second option does not exist.  If the second option did exist, then there would be a plethora of people capitalizing on it.<br>
<br>
Third, I have a problem with people that respond irrationally when someone questions why and what other people are doing.  I will leave that up to the rest of you to determine who responded that way to my earlier post.  <br>
<br>
Lastly, and this is intended more as a response to Mystala than anything, anonymity is a wonderful thing.  I knew there was going to be some person or people that would respond irrationally to my questioning.  Knowing that, I intentionally created an account to preserve that anonymity and to save myself the effort of putting anyone on my ignore list.  However, you must remember that not everybody participates in the message boards nor does everyone know that this particular thread exists.  In fact, my earlier post was my first.</font><P><P><i><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueayenaf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eayenaf</A> at: 5/11/01 7:52:05 am</FONT><br></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#F5F5DC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufayenae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fayenae</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>302</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>5/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>7:22:48 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Community Supporter</FONT><BR></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re:  Ragefire spawns:  reservation/rotation list</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Oh, and to address one more concern. No one has made it to the Rage part and not had the pearl, so far.  If someone does do that there will be NO waiting on them. They penalty is harsh, to the bottom they go.  Why?  Because they wasted our time and a spot on the list for a quest they were either A) not really into doing, or B)not capable of doing.<br>
<br>
So I make this warning to the people on the list without a pearl, get to it. Don't let your time sneak up on you and you not be ready, the penalty is not good.<br>
<br>
Hope this answers your question.  We will accept NO excuse from anyone who gets to Rage and has no pearl.<br>
