Troy,<br>
<br>
AsS far as switching places goes it is allowed as long as I do not see an abuse of it.  Yes, that is a good idea to not let non pearl holders do any switching (real real good idea in fact).  I use my judgement when it comes to switching names around, especially when it does not affect the people around the switchers.  If i ever hear of and selling spots both people will be booted from the spot.  People who leave the game are immediately removed.  Example is Jascenta; she made a huge post about her leaving so the day I read that i removed her.  If she returns to the game she can get her spot back, after she gets the pearl.  She made no note in her post to give he spot to anyone else. I have had some /tells asking for her spot, but she was removed so  in essence has not spot to give away.<br>
<br>
Trading is ok in the right circumstances, as I said.  Going out of town, sickness, emergency's, or anyhting along that line.  If you are leaving the game and are on the list you can give the spot to another ON THE LIST as in Lerwin's case.  He could not have given that spot to a person not on the list already.<br>
<br>
Hope this answers your question.</font><P>Fayenae <BR>
